Boil a full #kettle{}.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}.

Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Once cooked, transfer the steaks to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan on medium heat with a drizzle more oil if needed (no need to clean).

Add the garlic, @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} and @tomato puree{30%grams} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{75%grams}, @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar for the sauce{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{150%ml} into the pan. Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams} and @butter{20%grams} until melted.

Stir in the cooked pasta and mix until combined. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Thinly slice your steaks.

Share your creamy Cajun pasta between your #bowls{}.

Top with your sliced steak. Enjoy!